(b) The WOS/JV being established abroad by the CIC shall not be used
as a vehicle for raising resources for creating assets in India for the
Indian operations;

(d) If the WOS/JV has not undertaken any activity or such reports are
not forthcoming, the approvals given for setting up the WOS/JV
abroad shall be reviewed;

(iii) The level of net non-performing assets should be not more than 3% of
the total outstanding assets, including loans and advances taken
together;

(ii) An NBFC shall not adopt any restrictive practice of compelling its
customers to opt for a particular mutual fund product sponsored by it.
Its customers shall be allowed to exercise their own choice;
